article.headline: Portland State 58, Howard 53
article.story: WASHINGTON (AP) -- Seamus Boxley had 22 points and 16 rebounds to lead Portland State to a 58-53 victory over Howard University on Monday night. Boxley and Antone Jarrell combined to score six of the last eight points for the Vikings (2-2). Louis Ford had 14 points for the Bison (1-3). Jason Trotter gave Howard a 53-52 lead with a free throw with just over a minute to play. Boxley then made two free throws to put the Vikings ahead with 51 seconds remaining. Jarrell had 14 points and seven rebounds for Portland State, which shot 25 more free throws than Howard and held a 48-31 advantage on the boards.
